verses.verse: The Majesty and Condescension of God Praise the LORD! (Ps. 135:1) Praise, O servants of the LORD, Praise the name of the LORD!
((Dan. 2:20)) Blessed be the name of the LORD From this time forth and forevermore!
(Is. 59:19; Mal. 1:11) From the rising of the sun to its going down The LORD’s name is to be praised.
The LORD is (Ps. 97:9; 99:2) high above all nations, ((Ps. 8:1)) His glory above the heavens.
(Ps. 89:6; (Is. 57:15)) Who is like the LORD our God, Who dwells on high,
((Ps. 11:4; Is. 57:15)) Who humbles Himself to behold The things that are in the heavens and in the earth?
(1 Sam. 2:8; Ps. 107:41) He raises the poor out of the dust, And lifts the (Ps. 72:12) needy out of the ash heap,
That He may ((Job 36:7)) seat him with princes— With the princes of His people.
